==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Phrenitis
<hw>Phre*ni"tis</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., fr. Gr.
<grk>freni^tis</grk>, fr. <grk>frh`n</grk>, <grk>freno`s</grk>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>Inflammation of the brain, or of the
meninges of the brain, attended with acute fever and delirium; -- called
also <altname>cephalitis</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>See <er>Frenzy</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Phrenograph</ent>⟦br⟧
